caption.title: Temporal circulation of influenza A and B in Yucatan during the 2013.
caption.p: Influenza AH3N2 and A(H1N1)pdm09 were circulating at the same time from May until October. The A(H1N1)pdm09 peaked in circulation from June to October whereas the H3N2 peaked from July to October. At the end of the year, the influenza epidemic was predominated by influenza B virus.
